His photo of the unconscious Marine lying on the tank surrounded by his wounded brothers-in-arms now stands among the iconic images of the Vietnam War.
The picture of the wounded Marine was the largest photo in the feature, published as a two-page spread.
Then came the claim, which Rob and his siblings first saw in Bowden’s book, that the wounded Marine was someone else.
From this angle, we can see that the wounded Marine’s trousers have been loosened and pulled down to give access to the lower-back exit wound.
He also said that he was not interested in convincing anyone that he is the wounded Marine in the photo.